Minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Sabo Nanono has congratulated Prof Agboola Gambari on his appointment as the new Chief of Staff of president Buhari. He congratulated him via his twitter handle on Thursday. Institutions Gambari served before becoming President Buhari’s Chief of Staff He wrote, ‘I congratulate Prof.Ibrahim Agboola Gambari,CFR, on his Appointment as the Chief of Staff to President @MBuhari. ”A career diplomat who has scaled through unexpected boundaries and made difference. I wish you success, as you join the struggle in taking Nigeria to the Next Level.” I congratulate Prof.Ibrahim Agboola Gambari,CFR, on his Appointment as the Chief of Staff to President @MBuhari.A career diplomat who has scaled through unexpected boundaries and made difference.I wish you success, as you join the struggle in taking Nigeria to the Next Level. pic.twitter.com/tRxZHCOIHt